PROJECT SUMMARY
===============

Assignment: Data Extraction & Secure Validation
Student: Junior Frontend Developer (ALU Graduate)
Language: Python 3
Repository: alu_regex-data-extraction-{ibenito-cpu}

IMPLEMENTATION OVERVIEW
========================

✅ 8 Data Types Implemented (Exceeds requirement of 4):

1. Email Addresses
   • Formats: user@example.com, first.last@company.co.uk
   • Features: Masked output for privacy
   • Edge cases: Multiple TLDs, dots/hyphens/underscores

2. URLs
   • Formats: https://www.example.com, with paths and parameters
   • Features: Protocol validation, subdomain support
   • Edge cases: Different protocols, ports, query strings

3. Phone Numbers
   • Formats: (123) 456-7890, 123-456-7890, 123.456.7890
   • Features: Multiple separator styles
   • Edge cases: Parentheses, hyphens, dots, no separators

4. Credit Card Numbers
   • Formats: 1234 5678 9012 3456, 1234-5678-9012-3456
   • Features: Heavily masked (only last 4 digits shown)
   • Edge cases: Various separator formats

5. Time Values
   • Formats: 14:30 (24-hour), 2:30 PM (12-hour)
   • Features: Both format styles supported
   • Edge cases: AM/PM indicators, leading zeros

6. HTML Tags
   • Formats: <p>, <div class="x">, <img src="y" alt="z"/>
   • Features: Attributes, self-closing tags
   • Edge cases: Complex attributes, nested structures

7. Hashtags
   • Formats: #example, #ThisIsAHashtag
   • Features: Alphanumeric and underscores
   • Edge cases: Numbers, mixed case, position in text

8. Currency Amounts
   • Formats: $19.99, $1,234.56
   • Features: Comma separators, optional cents
   • Edge cases: Large amounts, decimal precision

SECURITY FEATURES
=================

✅ Comprehensive Input Validation:

• Length Limits: Max 100,000 characters (DoS prevention)
• Malicious Pattern Detection:
  - XSS: Script tags, JavaScript protocols, event handlers
  - SQL Injection: SQL keywords and injection patterns
  - Path Traversal: Directory traversal attempts
  - Code Execution: Eval, exec, system calls
  - Dangerous Protocols: file://, ftp://, data://

✅ Data Protection:
• Email masking: u***r@example.com
• Credit card masking: ************1234
• Sensitive data never exposed in logs

✅ Security Test Results: 8/8 PASSING
1. ✓ XSS Script Tag - BLOCKED
2. ✓ SQL Injection - BLOCKED
3. ✓ JavaScript Protocol - BLOCKED
4. ✓ Event Handler XSS - BLOCKED
5. ✓ Path Traversal - BLOCKED
6. ✓ Code Execution - BLOCKED
7. ✓ Dangerous Protocol - BLOCKED
8. ✓ Combined Attack - BLOCKED

